does anyone remember what the prizes were on queen for a day what did the women do to compete and how did they decide who won each day i can remember watching it and seeing the lady receive the drape crown etc but could not remember the rest of the show well i'm older than dirt remember watching this show with my grandmother it was really cheesy and probably was the prototype for hard luck shows today like extreme home makeover the host would have three women on each would tearfully tell her hard luck story they usually involved spoused who were unemployed a child or spouse with a near fatal disease with no money for medical attention around the holidays they never could afford christmas presents after all the hard luck stories were told the audience would vote via applause th with the levels recorded by one of those old applause meters the winner would then be crowned and draped with a noth eaten cloak with a fake ermine collar the prizes were pretty modest for today's standards new refrigerators full of food christmas toys for the kiddies etc and the final treat was the winner was driven in a limo to the beverly hills hotel for an overnight stay i'd love for an cable channel like tvland to show the old kinescopes of this show you'd die laughing EastEnders The Price Is Right The Amazing Race Game show Big Brother UK series 6 The Star Wars Holiday Special Eddie Murphy T___t The Adventures of Pete & Pete Survivor (TV series) The Critic My Parents are Aliens Winning Streak Christmas Fear Factor Piccolo Junior Saga Ken Jennings Press Your Luck Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma History of SNL:1980-1985 Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Confidence trick The Den (television) The Championships, Wimbledon Late Night with Conan O'Brien Clay Aiken Let's Make a Deal Girls Aloud Jackie Gleason Pitaten 1896 Summer Olympics Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Television in the United States Marriage Big Brother (USA TV series) Stomach cancer The Joker's Wild The Weakest Lin